Class Experiment

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.nerdherd.Model.Experiment

  • public class Experiment
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a single experiment. Which should be modified through ExperimentManager to preserve state between client and database

      • Experiment

        public Experiment(java.lang.String experimentId,
                  java.lang.String title,
                  java.lang.String description,
                  java.lang.String ownerId,
                  Region region,
                  int minimumTrials,
                  int type,
                  com.google.firebase.Timestamp date,
                  boolean locationRequired,
                  boolean published)
        Experiment class Object
        Parameters:
        experimentId - String - unique Id of the Experiment
        title - String - title of the experiment
        description - String - description of the experiment
        ownerId - String - unique owned Id associated with a UserProfile - this user created and controls the experiment
        region - Region - a region object containing a description, point location, and range around that location
        minimumTrials - int - minimum amount of trials for the experiment to be published
        type - int - enumerated type of experiment; Binomial=0, Count=1, Measurement=2, Non-Negative=3
        date - TimeStamp - firebase timestamp object to keep control of when experiment was created
        locationRequired - Boolean - dictates whether or not location data must be included with submitted trial
        published - Boolean - current publish status of experiment. Can publish and unpublish as needed. This removes it from public view.
